snippet.textDisplay: Never ever would I take an "entourage" to pick out a dress for a special occasion.  The last thing I would want to have to contend with is snide, snarky, cutting comments from anyone, especially people who claim to be and are supposed to be people who care about me ....... and my feelings.  I doubt I would even want my mother with me trying to pushed her opinion on me as well.  And, If I'm the one paying for the dress, I think I would be inclined to want to have everyone to have the same surprise and the groom and expect that they be on their best behavior and save their criticisms for after I am long gone on my honey moon ..... and even then KEEP IT TO THEMSELVES, because at that point I really wouldn't give a rat's ass or care about knowing whether they liked my pick of dress.
